# OpenClaw .env example
#
# Quick start:
# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (for local runs from this repo), OR to `~/.openclaw/.env` (for launchd/systemd daemons).
# 2) Fill only the values you use.
# 3) Keep real secrets out of git.
#
# Env-source precedence for environment variables (highest -> lowest):
# process env, ./.env, ~/.openclaw/.env, then openclaw.json `env` block.
# Existing non-empty process env vars are not overridden by dotenv/config env loading.
# Note: direct config keys (for example `gateway.auth.token` or channel tokens in openclaw.json)
# are resolved separately from env loading and often take precedence over env fallbacks.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gateway auth + paths
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required if the gateway binds beyond loopback. Leave blank to have OpenClaw
# auto-generate a token on first start, or provide your own using
# `openssl rand -hex 32`. The gateway will refuse to start if this is set to
# the documented example placeholder, so never copy-paste an example value
# from docs or tutorials into this file verbatim.
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=

# Optional alternative auth mode (use token OR password).
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD=

# Optional path overrides (defaults shown for reference).
# OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=~/.openclaw
# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=~/.openclaw/openclaw.json
# OPENCLAW_HOME=~
# Docker setup stores auth profile encryption key material outside the mounted
# OpenClaw state dir and mounts this host directory into the container.
# OPENCLAW_AUTH_PROFILE_SECRET_DIR=/absolute/path/to/.openclaw-auth-profile-secrets

# Allowlist of extra directories that `$include` directives in openclaw.json may
# resolve files from. Path-list separated (':' on POSIX, ';' on Windows). Each
# entry is tilde-expanded. Without this, `$include` is confined to the directory
# containing openclaw.json.
# OPENCLAW_INCLUDE_ROOTS=/etc/openclaw/shared:~/.openclaw/shared

# Optional: import missing keys from your login shell profile.
# OPENCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1
# OPENCLAW_SHELL_ENV_TIMEOUT_MS=15000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Model provider API keys (set at least one)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_OPENAI_KEY=sk-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_GEMINI_KEY=...
# OPENAI_API_KEY_1=...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_1=...
# GEMINI_API_KEY_1=...
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
# OPENAI_API_KEYS=sk-1,sk-2
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS=sk-ant-1,sk-ant-2
# GEMINI_API_KEYS=key-1,key-2

# Optional additional providers
# ZAI_API_KEY=...
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...
# TOKENHUB_API_KEY=...
# LKEAP_API_KEY=...
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=...
# SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Channels (only set what you enable)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABCDEF...
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...
# Uncomment + fill both to have setup.sh run `channels add --channel slack`
# for you (idempotent — skipped if Slack is already configured). Requires a
# Slack app with Socket Mode enabled; see "Wire up Slack" in DEPLOYMENT.md.
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...

# Optional channel env fallbacks
# MATTERMOST_BOT_TOKEN=...
# MATTERMOST_URL=https://chat.example.com
# ZALO_BOT_TOKEN=...
# OPENCLAW_TWITCH_ACCESS_TOKEN=oauth:...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tools + voice/media (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BRAVE_API_KEY=...
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-...
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...

# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...
# XI_API_KEY=...  # alias for ElevenLabs
# INWORLD_API_KEY=...
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Multi-agent / advanced (optional — kept commented; edit only if you need it)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This repo doubles as a TEMPLATE: copy it once per agent. These knobs only
# matter when you run more than one agent deployment on the SAME host — each
# then needs a distinct identity so its containers and its /home/node volume
# don't collide. (setup.sh does NOT touch this section — it only uncomments the
# auto-configured block further below.)
#
# COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME namespaces this deployment's containers and its home
# volume. It defaults to this directory's name, so cloning into distinct
# directories (openclaw-support/, openclaw-sales/, ...) already isolates
# agents. Set it explicitly only if two clones would share a directory name.
# COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=my-agent
#
# The Claude-CLI home volume is named "<project>_home" automatically (unique per
# deployment). Set this ONLY to pin an exact volume — e.g. to attach an existing
# one restored from a backup on another host.
# OPENCLAW_HOME_VOLUME=
#
# Extra published ports (base compose file; loopback-only by default via
# docker-compose.extra.yml's `ports: !reset []` — see DEPLOYMENT.md). Only
# relevant if you re-enable these ports for a channel that needs them.
# OPENCLAW_BRIDGE_PORT=18790
# OPENCLAW_MSTEAMS_PORT=3978
#
# Container timezone (affects log timestamps and any time-aware agent logic).
# OPENCLAW_TZ=UTC
#
# OpenTelemetry export (outbound OTLP/HTTP from the gateway) — leave unset
# unless you're wiring this deployment into an existing OTel collector.
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_TRACES_ENDPOINT=
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_METRICS_ENDPOINT=
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_LOGS_ENDPOINT=
# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL=http/protobuf
# OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=
# OTEL_SEMCONV_STABILITY_OPT_IN=
# OPENCLAW_OTEL_PRELOADED=
#
# Claude web session auth (alternative to CLI OAuth login) — leave unset
# unless you know you need it.
# CLAUDE_AI_SESSION_KEY=
# CLAUDE_WEB_SESSION_KEY=
# CLAUDE_WEB_COOKIE=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker deployment overrides (auto-configured by setup.sh; see DEPLOYMENT.md
# for the full setup this instance uses: pre-built pinned image, claude-cli
# agent runtime, loopback bind, project-local data dirs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# setup.sh uncomments every KEY=value line from here to the end of the file.
# Single source of truth for the OpenClaw version. Bump here only; the pulled
# image tag, the local Dockerfile FROM base, and the built image tag all derive
# from it. Check tags at ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw.
# OPENCLAW_VERSION=2026.7.1
#
# Stock (npm-only agents): pull the published image directly.
# OPENCLAW_IMAGE=ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw:${OPENCLAW_VERSION}
#
# Python/OS-dep agents (this repo's default): build the committed Dockerfile,
# which layers pip + the per-agent Python hook onto the SAME version.
# OPENCLAW_IMAGE=openclaw-deploy-py:${OPENCLAW_VERSION}

# Project-local, self-contained data dirs instead of ~/.openclaw — makes the
# whole deployment portable (copy .env + this dir to move/back up).
# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_DIR=./.openclaw-data/config
# OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR=./.openclaw-data/workspace
# OPENCLAW_AUTH_PROFILE_SECRET_DIR=./.openclaw-data/auth-secrets

# loopback = no inbound network exposure at all (right choice when the only
# interaction modes are outbound channels like Slack, plus local terminal
# access via `docker compose run openclaw-cli`). Use lan/tailnet if you need
# the Control UI or another client to reach the gateway over the network.
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_BIND=loopback

# Ensures every `docker compose` invocation picks up docker-compose.extra.yml
# automatically, without needing -f flags.
# COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.yml:docker-compose.extra.yml
